text: Northern Fury F.C. is a soccer club from Townsville, Queensland, Australia. The club was founded in 2008 and competed in the A-League as North Queensland Fury FC. On 1 March 2011, the club was removed from the league due to financial instability. On 3 October 2012, the club was re-formed as Northern Fury FC after it was granted a license to play in the NPL Queensland.http://www.townsvillebulletin.com.au/article/2012/10/03/365141_sport.html Northern Fury play their home fixtures at Townsville Sports Reserve. == Honours == ===Minor Trophies/Honours=== * Queensland Nickel Cup ** 2009/10 (NQ Fury V's Gold Coast United: {Contested Over 3 League Fixtures} NQ Fury W2/D0/L1) * Chief Minister's Cup : – 2009 (3–2 V's Adelaide United – Played In Darwin/NT 02/07/09) ==References== Category:A-League Men Category:Soccer clubs in Queensland
